{
  "texts": [
    "Opinion terms (o) can be conveyed either explicitly or implicitly.",
    "Explicit expressions involve words or phrases expressing a positive, negative, or neutral attitude toward a specific aspect or category.",
    "It can include adjectives, adverbs, or verbs that indicate a particular evaluation or attitude.",
    "Implicit expressions do not directly state a positive or negative attitude but imply a particular evaluation or attitude.",
    "It can include more subtle language, such as humor, irony, slang, or other nuanced phrasing that allows for multiple interpretations."
  ]
}